Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.76,0:00:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,okay now i'm here i had the secret of the universe someplace i don't know what i do\Nlost it someplace where'd the music go
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.00,0:01:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the music calibrates at 700 i just want people to know what 700 sounds like and feels like\N700 makes you cry so it's not good to play right before you're going to speak
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.98,0:01:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that was a problem i had throughout my life trying to avoid beauty because it breaks you up and\Nso that's one of the pathways to god you see because that which expresses itself is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.12,0:02:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,incredible\Nbeauty first becomes noticeable to people very often by aesthetic beauty you know to be out in
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.43,0:02:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the forest to be in a great cathedral to hear a magnificent symphony to hear a beautiful opera\Ngorgeous music is one of the first sensitivities even so even in the beginning god has really
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.84,0:02:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,experienced this as as beauty you don't realize it's god you just think it's beauty\Npretty soon you begin to experience the divinity of all things
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.31,0:03:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the sound of divinity then begins to shine forth and within all phenomena\Nso today we'll we'll go through a series of slides having to do with the evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.96,0:03:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,which is sort of original and uh first appeared on the planet in the mid 90s 95 until current time and kind\N食想も締結 물�行 시간 이llow이 λburst해
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.75,0:03:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,has had no way of telling truth from falsehood the human mind is innately\Nincapable of it by virtue of its structure the structure of the ego is
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.72,0:03:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,such that one cannot ascertain truth or falsehood one can only deal and\Nperception observation probability and opinion the mind itself then eventually
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.59,0:04:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,evolves over great courses of time so see how the ego life appear first\Nappears on the planet as first appearance of life on our calibrated
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.25,0:04:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,scale of one to a thousand we would say be is one bacteria appear back eons ago\Nthis hot hot lava spinning through the universe cooled down and developed the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.26,0:04:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,crust condition suitable to protoplasmic life took eons the energy field of\Nconsciousness which whose source is divinity itself
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.67,0:04:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,on earth...\Nmanifest becoming manifest as consciousness the infinite power of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.62,0:04:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness interacting with materiality created life and as much as\Nconsciousness is the source of all of life the life merely appeared on this
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.49,0:05:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,planet but it was already present as consciousness itself the first bacteria\Nthen calibrated at one and then we go through the animal kingdom through
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.05,0:05:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution and we have slides which will demonstrate the evolution of\Nconsciousness over great eons of time out of which came early man Neanderthal
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.98,0:05:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,man calibrated about 70 homo erectus and then you come up through Heidelberg man\Nand then finally the last modern man 600,000 years ago out of Ethiopia and
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.50,0:05:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,then we see the evolution of consciousness over the centuries 190 it\Nstood at 190 for a whole millennium through the 1800s early 1900s and
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.67,0:05:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,finally in 1980 late 1980\Njumped from 190 to 205 probably the most important phenomena that has
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.77,0:06:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,occurred on this planet but since it since life began completely unnoticed by\Nanyone that it signaled a new era because 190 below 200 is quite critical
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.35,0:06:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand I teach the pathway of devotional non-duality that is the devotion to non-duality that is the devotion to non-duality that is the devotion to\Nthe truth itself no matter what it's rather radical it's more akin to Zen than
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.20,0:06:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,anything perhaps so crossing over 200 net a whole new paradigm of reality it will\Ncheck how that evolved so how did life stay alive on a planet to which was
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.72,0:07:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,unfriendly like be planting a bacterium in Mars would have a tough time nothing\Non Mars that favors life at all to survive then life had to be totally self-interested life had to be self-interested life had to be totally self-interested
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.81,0:07:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,towards me, my life.\NThe bacteria's not interested in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.11,0:07:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Paramecium is not interested in you.\NThe mouse is not interested in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.33,0:07:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The donkey's not interested in you.\NThe lion's not interested in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.75,0:07:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What's my favorite reptile, that horrible reptile?\NThe Komodo dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.10,0:07:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The Komodo dragon is not interested in you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.18,0:07:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the core of the ego is survival, self-interest,\Nand the evolution of the animal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.00,0:07:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Then evolved to more sophisticated ways of survival,\Nbut it was still me then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.55,0:08:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,On top of the old animal brain was a prefrontal cortex,\Nan add-on addition.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.62,0:08:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And you notice that the animal brain wasn't removed and replaced.\NThe animal remained, and we just added a prefrontal cortex.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.86,0:08:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The prefrontal cortex\Nnow came to serve, therefore, animal instincts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.37,0:08:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,To the ego, the prefrontal cortex\Nwas just another tool of survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.37,0:08:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, a consciousness level below 200 means me.\NSo let's do the first slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.12,0:08:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You're all familiar with the map of consciousness,\Nwhich is fuzzy and unreadable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.98,0:08:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we could turn down these...\NCan we turn down the light a little bit
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.13,0:08:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because we're washing it out?\NAnyway, this has become extremely well known.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.23,0:09:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all over the world now, all over the internet.\NAnd it's sort of like E equals MC squared
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.23,0:09:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's the open sesame\Nto a whole new realization of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.23,0:09:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still sort of illegible, isn't it?\NThis side is sort of shady and sort of fuzzy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.79,0:09:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe all we have to do is focus it a little better, you know?\NWell, you're all familiar with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.01,0:09:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody here is familiar with it, right?\NAnd those of you who have been through the lectures before.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.53,0:09:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So life starts way down here at total self-interest,\Nand it still prevails, let's say,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.74,0:09:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,75% of the world calibrates below 200.\NSo this we could call one's animal nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.25,0:09:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,One's animal nature, all these behaviors are common to the animal.\NThen you add the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.75,0:10:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the animal merely uses the intellect\Nto make atomic bombs to blow you up,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.00,0:10:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to make better munitions,\Nnew ways to deceive you,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.46,0:10:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,sophistries that are extremely clever.\NThe human mind can't tell good from evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.55,0:10:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Not capable.\NDoesn't know integrity at 460
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.14,0:10:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,from a megalomaniac at 90.\NDoesn't know a megalomaniac who hates people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.55,0:10:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So the great leaders that people all give their life for,\Nto them, the people are dirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.00,0:10:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And they'll tell you so.\NIn the end, they'll tell you,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.66,0:11:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,all the Germans should die, they lost the war.\NThe Chinese don't deserve to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.78,0:11:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Just kill them all.\NTotal, total destructiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.85,0:11:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And the human mind can't tell one from the other.\NIt's like you don't know a Komodo dragon from your kitty cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.97,0:11:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's serious.\NThat is serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.97,0:11:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It also explains human history.\NFrom a spiritual viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.53,0:11:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,then, this is the animal kingdom,\Nwhich prevails, persists in man as the so-called ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.08,0:11:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of much spiritual guilt,\Nand the reason that a lot of the traditional religions have lost many followers,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.24,0:11:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is they had a sort of morbid quality.\NWorshipping sin, and penance, and groveling,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.37,0:11:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and sort of the downside, sort of morbid,\Nsort of medieval Spanish morbid.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.37,0:12:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Celebrating agony and suffering.\NYou know, so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.55,0:12:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people lost interest in that.\NNow,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.74,0:12:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,if the way to God was sin, guilt, and suffering,\Nthen you could wallow around here and find God.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.74,0:12:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The only problem is God is up this end of the chart,\Nnot at this end.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.74,0:12:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So that cloth and ashes will get you into egotism.\NYou realize what a narcissistic self-indulgence that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.05,0:12:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Lord, look how I've suffered,\Nand how I've been wicked.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.05,0:12:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you'd get off it.\NGive me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.05,0:12:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus, all that sniveling.\NCalling attention to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.53,0:12:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What an ego inflation that is.\NTo the universe, your dopey little sins don't even register.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.53,0:13:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Going on your knees till they bleed on the streets of the city,\Ncobblestone by cobblestone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.53,0:13:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a break.\NTurn off the movie, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.91,0:13:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Get real.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.03,0:13:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see now,\Nlet's do the next slide,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.03,0:13:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,85% of mankind calibrates below 200.\NOh, this is a new one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.03,0:13:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot about this one.\NThis one is backwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.92,0:13:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This was from George Zielinski.\NGeorge, where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.57,0:13:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It is new.\NWell, you know, I did the Calvary Scale of Consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.57,0:13:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, using kinesiology,\Nand expressed it in logarithmic numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.57,0:13:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Other mathematicians have come in.\NYou know, I'm not very left-brained.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.57,0:13:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I'm not left-brained at all.\NI tell them I'm not left-brained.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.57,0:14:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So they substituted their left brain for mine,\Nand this is a new calibration
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.57,0:14:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,based on more advanced mathematics.\NSo this is the scale of consciousness graphed out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.62,0:14:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And you will see,\Nand the explanation is at the bottom,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.62,0:14:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,which you can't read either,\Nbut you don't need to know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.62,0:14:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very complicated.\NDon't show them that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.62,0:14:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll get there.\NYou could put it up higher, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.62,0:14:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,However, you'll notice\Nthat at consciousness level 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.88,0:14:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you see it's steady.\NAll of a sudden, at 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.26,0:14:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you have a step increase.\NThis is the level of integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.26,0:14:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you are just the animal,\Nme, me, me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.26,0:14:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And then all of a sudden,\Nyou discover there's other people in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.26,0:14:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And how about you?\NOh, you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.26,0:14:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NYou see a bend.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.19,0:14:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the world of the intellect,\Nthe 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.19,0:14:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when you get up to 500,\Nthere's a shift of paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.19,0:15:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What's real in the 400s\Nis no longer real in the 500s.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.50,0:15:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty with science,\Nwhich is stuck in the 400s,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.50,0:15:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is the Newtonian paradigm.\NYou can't jump the paradigm at 500
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.50,0:15:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because there you jump from pseudo-objectivity\Nto subjectivity,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.50,0:15:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,which has actually been going all along\Nwith the illusion that you're being objective,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.50,0:15:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a subjective condition,\Nan opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.50,0:15:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And here you get honest,\Nand you realize,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.50,0:15:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,hey, that's subjective.\NAnd then you get the calibrated scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.50,0:15:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is new from George,\Nand I just thought we'd throw it in
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.58,0:15:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because it does show a change\Nin the speed at which things rise.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.58,0:15:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NIt would take a long time to explain
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.51,0:15:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,what that all means,\Nbut anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.51,0:15:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,these are all of mankind.\NHere's all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.51,0:15:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The number of people\Nwho calibrate below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.10,0:15:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the mass of mankind,\Nwhich shades off into the shade over there,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.10,0:16:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,into the dark.\NMove it a little bit more to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.19,0:16:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,1,000, there's practically nobody here.\NThere's practically nobody here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.19,0:16:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, from 600 up,\Nthere's practically nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.19,0:16:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And when they do hit that state of consciousness,\Nhalf of them leave the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.19,0:16:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't leave the planet.\NIt's just that you're no longer
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.19,0:16:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,a member of the planet,\Nand then the body falls over.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.19,0:16:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Which was a mistake.\NAnyway, you should have left it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.19,0:16:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to fall over there.\NYou didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.19,0:16:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So 540 is unconditional love.\NUnconditional love is reached
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.92,0:16:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,by 0.4% of the world's population.\N0.4.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.73,0:16:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you want to experience love,\Nyou better take it with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.88,0:16:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,500 is the new paradigm,\Nthe shift to love itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.79,0:16:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,4% of the world's population\Ncalibrates over 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.05,0:17:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody talks about love,\Nbut what they're really talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.05,0:17:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is the solar plexus desiringness,\Nattachment.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.18,0:17:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's a love that's an emotion\Nthat goes from me to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.53,0:17:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you leave, I'll kill you, bitch.\NThat's an attachment.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.28,0:17:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A clutchingness, a fervent clutchingness,\Na holdingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.28,0:17:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and a sexual objectness,\Ncontrolness, ownership.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.92,0:17:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's volatile and it's explosive.\NThe divorce rate in the United States is 50%.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.92,0:17:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we're not talking about that love.\NBecause that's coming out of the solar plexus.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.24,0:17:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming out of the heart is 500.\N540 is unconditional.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.24,0:17:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And 540 is...\NSo the levels of love
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.24,0:17:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is a way of being in the world.\NIt's a way of being.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.24,0:17:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not an emotion at all.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.43,0:18:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It leaves emotionality.\NNow it's a way of being.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.43,0:18:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That you notice the beauty of the plant\Nand you give it a little love as you go by
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.43,0:18:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's your way of being in the world.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.31,0:18:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Lovingness is like kindness.\NIt's a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.48,0:18:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's the way you relate to everything in the world.\NThe animals, the trees, the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.48,0:18:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.18,0:18:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we said here's 50...\NHere's the way the world's population is spread out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.67,0:18:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,15% calibrate over 200.\N85% below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.67,0:18:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it that the 85% don't swamp us?\NWell, they do with taxes, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.47,0:18:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the productivity of these 15\Nthat keep the other 85 going.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.47,0:18:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do these people get their job?\NThey get it from these people here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.47,0:18:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Henry Ford.\NAndrew Carnegie.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.81,0:19:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Thomas Edison.\NOne brilliant thought
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.81,0:19:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,creates more capital out there\Nthan all the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.81,0:19:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Than all the productivity of many nations\Non the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.81,0:19:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In the world.\NOut of Thomas Edison's head.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.36,0:19:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So where is the capital of the capitalist people?\NThe naive think it's money in a bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.36,0:19:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got nothing to do with money in the bank.\NNothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.43,0:19:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with what's up here.\NThomas Edison created more wealth
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.58,0:19:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and one brilliant idea with electricity\Nspread across the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.80,0:19:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Electricity produces more jobs.\NCreated more.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.80,0:19:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So capital is a brilliance in the head.\NEmpire State Building arose as an inspiration.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.50,0:19:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, how about the biggest building,\Nthe tallest building in the world, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.18,0:19:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a concept.\NThe telephone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.24,0:19:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The airplane.\NSo the country that everybody hates
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.24,0:19:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're so rich,\Nthe big capitalist, horrible fat pig
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.24,0:20:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that smokes cigars.\NWhat does he look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.24,0:20:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He looks like an idea that somebody said.\NThat's where capitalism is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.00,0:20:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's...\Nthe ownership of genius and creativity.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.22,0:20:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And our country supports that.\NThat's why you have Frank Lloyd Wright,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.63,0:20:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you have the invention of the airplane,\Nthe computer chip, the telephone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.78,0:20:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Just about everything you look at and use\Nis an American invention
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.10,0:20:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,out of creativity and invention.\NEurope invented the printing press.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.80,0:20:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't use that anymore.\NI used to get a big thing from the Medical Society
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.53,0:20:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,for the year, you know,\Nand now I get a little funny-looking thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.53,0:20:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what they use it for.\NI ask you, what do you call this thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.53,0:20:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,CD, they call it.\NIs that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.53,0:21:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnyway, it makes a really good sauce
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.53,0:21:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,over a coffee cup.\NThat's what I use it for.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.53,0:21:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo those are exponents of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.79,0:21:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The people in 15% have power.\NOne Thomas Edison counterbalances
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.93,0:21:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,probably half of Africa,\Nmaybe all of Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.93,0:21:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,By sheer genius, productivity,\Nand power of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.85,0:21:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So these 15%, then,\Nare what keep the calibrated
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.29,0:21:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,overall level of consciousness of mankind.\NSo we said it stayed at 190
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.72,0:21:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,through all the centuries,\Nall the Black Plague,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.72,0:21:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the horrible wars,\Nthe Napoleonic era.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.00,0:21:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It went all through,\Nand then the late 1980s
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.00,0:21:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,at about the same time\Nas the Harmonic Concordance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.00,0:21:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In the late 1980s,\Nit went through
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.00,0:21:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and it suddenly jumped from 190,\Nwhich is non-integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.00,0:21:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and certain death.\NWe would have ended up
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.00,0:21:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in an atomic destruction of humanity\Nat 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.00,0:22:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It jumped to 205.\NAt 190, the great bomb
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.32,0:22:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in case Russia lost the war\Nthat was going to destroy
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.32,0:22:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,all of mankind\Nwould have gone off.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.32,0:22:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,At 190, it'll go off\Nbecause out of arrogance.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.68,0:22:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody deserves to live\Nif we lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.68,0:22:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll take you with them.\NEverybody who does swimming rescue
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.86,0:22:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,knows that.\NAnybody here got a swimming
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.86,0:22:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,rescuer badge?\NEverybody's going to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.86,0:22:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,.\NThey'll take you down with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.86,0:22:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the first thing you learn.\NApproach them from the back
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.86,0:22:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because the drowning man\Nwill take you with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.86,0:22:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo in the late 1980s
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.45,0:22:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,at about the time\Nof the Harmonic Concordance,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.45,0:22:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I never did get the date,\Nit jumped from 190 to 205.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.56,0:22:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You might say\Nthe collective karma of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.56,0:22:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,because aside from downward things,\Nman also did heroic
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.98,0:22:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and great things as well.\NAnd at 205,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.98,0:22:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a whole different ballgame.\NThen it stayed at 205
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.40,0:23:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,for some 30 years.\N1980, no, not 30 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.40,0:23:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,25 years.\NThen on November 8th,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.40,0:23:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we were giving a lecture\Nin San Francisco.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.40,0:23:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was the date\Nof the next Harmonic Concordance.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.69,0:23:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We got a thing in the email.\NSomething like 515 to 518
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.09,0:23:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,was the Harmonic Concordance.\NWell, we had a big crowd in Frisco.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.09,0:23:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.\NSo we all,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.09,0:23:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,what did we do?\NNico chanted the Lotus Sutra
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.35,0:23:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and we all prayed for world peace\Nand then we all meditated together.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.35,0:23:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's on.\NIt's recorded on videotape.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.35,0:23:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Susan, who is my right arm,\Nand I at 515
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.57,0:23:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated the energy level\Nof all of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.57,0:23:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was 205,\Nthe same as it had been
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.57,0:23:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,for 25 years.\NThen after,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.31,0:23:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,at 530 San Francisco time,\Nwe recalibrated it
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.76,0:24:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was 207.\NI said,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.76,0:24:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,are we imagining this or what?\NAll right,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.44,0:24:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see what the consciousness\Nlevel of mankind is now.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.75,0:24:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask here.\NIt's still at 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.75,0:24:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NIt stays in places
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.75,0:24:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,for long periods of time.\NBut 207 means,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.81,0:24:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,first of all,\Nsurvival.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.81,0:24:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Less than 200 means eventually\Nnon-survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.81,0:24:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So for all of life on this planet,\Nthe fact that the consciousness level
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.81,0:24:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of mankind is 207\Nto me is the signal
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.04,0:24:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of the oncoming of a new\Nconsciousness level
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.09,0:24:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,for mankind.\NSo we know that above 200 then
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.77,0:24:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,makes your arm go strong\Nwith kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.77,0:24:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200 makes you go weak.\NAnd the higher levels of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.28,0:24:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of course,\Nare documented in the books
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.28,0:25:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that I've done.\NOkay,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.28,0:25:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,so let's move on to the next one.\NOh,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.59,0:25:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,yes.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.81,0:25:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,\Nwe were talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.81,0:25:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,how to transcend the ego.\NDevotional non-duality means
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.81,0:25:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the way to the realization\Nof divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.81,0:25:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,by transcending the ego.\NConsequently,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.18,0:25:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,one has to understand something\Nabout how to disassemble the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.18,0:25:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego,\Nwe said,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.81,0:25:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is the remnant of the animal nature\Nwithin us.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.81,0:25:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's no point in vilifying it.\NThere's no point in wallowing in guilt
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.81,0:25:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and mortification and penance.\NInstead,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.98,0:25:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to own it\Nas your fuzzy little animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.98,0:25:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot my bear today.\NWhere's my bear?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.16,0:25:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I left it.\NIt's your fuzzy little animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.16,0:25:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And instead of hating it,\Nwhat you do is
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.16,0:26:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you own it.\NBecause if you don't vilify it
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.28,0:26:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't demonize it,\Nyou can just say,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.76,0:26:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,oh,\Nit's my inherited genetic,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.76,0:26:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it's my genetic inheritance\Nas a member of the animal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.76,0:26:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Man's difficulty is\Nthat he's born with
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.15,0:26:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness of the animal\Nand the brain of an animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.18,0:26:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But he unfortunately has\Nthe consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.18,0:26:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and the awareness of divinity.\NSo he's halfway between
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.18,0:26:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the animal and the angel.\NThat puts man in one tough place.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.69,0:26:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So St. Peter at the gate,\NI've always advised him,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.09,0:26:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody who comes from this planet\Nor is just passing by,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.09,0:26:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,because anybody who's lived out\Na human lifetime deserves
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.09,0:26:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,at least 20 points of karmic credit\Non his record
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.39,0:26:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to have survived on this planet.\NAnd people don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.90,0:26:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,what we mean yet.\NBut as you get older,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.90,0:27:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize.\NAll right,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.90,0:27:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,so instead of vilifying the ego\Nas a source of sin and guilt,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.90,0:27:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,it's really your animal.\NAnd it's good to give your animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.08,0:27:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Mine's name is Fuzzy.\NAnd if somebody gets in front of you
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.47,0:27:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in traffic,\Nyou say,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.47,0:27:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,we hate them,\Ndon't we, Fuzzy?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.47,0:27:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NWe want to kill them,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.42,0:27:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,don't we?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.43,0:27:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course they deserve it.\NYou know that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.43,0:27:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,because we're right.\NBecause we're right
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.43,0:27:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're wrong.\NWe're always right
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.57,0:27:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and the others are always wrong.\NBut that's our little secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.14,0:27:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll run for office\Nbecause we're going to help
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.14,0:28:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the United States.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.14,0:28:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That one made the arm go weak.\NWell.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.14,0:28:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All right,\Nso if you accept that Fuzzy
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.14,0:28:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is into survival,\Nand the survivor is willing
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.14,0:28:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to lie,\Ndeceive,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.14,0:28:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,cheat,\Npad the bill,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.14,0:28:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,lie cleverly,\Nbecome a sophist,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.26,0:28:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,a sophist,\Npeople who know how to distort
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.55,0:28:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth cleverly\Nso that it is persuasive
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.55,0:28:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and appeals to the naive,\Nappeals to the naive.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.55,0:28:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We are clever, aren't we?\NLook how many people voted for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.60,0:28:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrate all the candidates\Nfor president
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.75,0:28:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and you'll not sleep as well\Nas you did before.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.75,0:28:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So how does the ego\Nget to be this way?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.41,0:29:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the ego is the animal.\NOne thing the animal has to learn
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.41,0:29:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is what is good\Nand what is bad for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.41,0:29:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's our translation.\NThere's things that are good
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.50,0:29:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and things that are not so good.\NSo you have to identify
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.50,0:29:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,already you're into duality.\NThere's the me
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.50,0:29:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's the that.\NAnd now you begin to judge the that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.56,0:29:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's either dangerous or friendly.\NYou can either eat it
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.56,0:29:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,or it'll eat you.\NIt'll eat you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.56,0:29:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The animal doesn't really care.\NThe animal doesn't really kill anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.69,0:29:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you see.\NSo that gets us into the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.00,0:29:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that the way people see the world\Nis a projection of their own mind
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.00,0:29:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that has nothing to do with reality.\NAnimals don't kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.31,0:29:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They have lunch.\NNow, if your lunch had legs
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.31,0:29:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and kept running away,\Nyou make it make it stop running away
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.31,0:29:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can eat it\Nand you got to bite it back here
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.31,0:29:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it lays still\Nand you can eat the freaking thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.31,0:29:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If it would just lay still,\Nyou wouldn't have to bother doing that,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.31,0:29:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,which takes all kinds of energy.\NYou must get tired
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.01,0:30:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,of running all across the plains in Africa\Nwhere it's hot as all get out
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.01,0:30:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,just to get your dinner.\NHow would you like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.01,0:30:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as you go for your hamburger,\Nit runs across the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.01,0:30:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Come here.\NClaus, you need Claus
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.99,0:30:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to grab that freaking cheeseburger\Nbefore it runs out the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.99,0:30:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus, other people are after your cheeseburger,\Nso you've got to get them off the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.70,0:30:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can see where the animal's at.\NIt's got to be the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.38,0:30:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got to be the way it is.\NAnd we see the same motivation,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.42,0:30:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and the same phenomena in mankind.\NNow, the reason we have this
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.89,0:30:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is because to transcend the ego,\Nyou have to understand how the ego operates.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.89,0:30:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego operates out of the animals\Nhaving to recognize a thing as a friend or a foe.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.89,0:31:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's either edible or not edible.\NYou can mate with it or not mate with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.61,0:31:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So life becomes very simple.\NIt's mateable, eatable,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.61,0:31:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,or defeatable.\NNow, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.80,0:31:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the difficulty with the animal's calibration\Nand classification of people
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.80,0:31:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is that it sets up the mind then,\Npicks a dividing line
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.38,0:31:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and creates a duality\Nof this and of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.53,0:31:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of good and of bad,\Nof good and evil, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.03,0:31:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an illusion because,\Nto consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.03,0:31:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see that\Nthere are not really
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.03,0:31:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,two conditions, heat versus cold,\Ngood versus bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.03,0:31:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,As you get closer to enlighten me,\Nyou see there's only a oneness,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.03,0:31:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,only a oneness.\NAnd there's degrees of presence
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.03,0:32:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of certain qualities.\NThere is no opposites of heat and cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.48,0:32:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Heat is either present or not present.\NIf heat is present, we call it hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.93,0:32:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Less and less heat,\Nhere there's an absence of heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.93,0:32:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So there isn't heat and non-heat,\Nthere isn't heat and cold,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.66,0:32:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,there's heat to a varying degree of presence.\NThere's only one variable, heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.75,0:32:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, we can do the same thing with value.\NIf you want a thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.78,0:32:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you call it precious.\NThere isn't good and bad,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.78,0:32:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,there's either you want it\Nor you don't want it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.78,0:32:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The degree of your wantingness\Nis a single variable,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.78,0:32:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,just like heat.\NOkay, let's go to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.98,0:32:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Another simple one to see\Nis there are not two opposites
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.46,0:32:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of light versus darkness.\NThere is only one variable,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.66,0:32:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence of light\Nand the degree to which light is present.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.66,0:33:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There is light,\Nand as light fades out,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.66,0:33:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,we call it dark,\Nbut it is not its opposite,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.66,0:33:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,it's its absence.\NThat's important because
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.81,0:33:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the same thing applies to truth.\NTruth is either present or it is absent.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.81,0:33:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is either present or it's absent.\NThere are not two opposite qualities,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.08,0:33:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,like good and evil,\Ntrue and not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.08,0:33:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so there's one variable, light.\NLet's go over to the left-hand side.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.44,0:33:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodness.\NThere isn't goodness and badness.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.66,0:33:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,There is lots of goodness,\Nand good, as it fades away,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.78,0:33:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,we give it a different name.\NBut the fact that it has a nom,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.78,0:33:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that we denote it\Nby a different word
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.78,0:33:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean that it's an opposite.\NTo get beyond the duality of the opposites,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.14,0:33:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to see there's only a oneness.\NAlright, many of you have seen these lectures before,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.42,0:34:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're just going to recapitulate them.\NHmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.01,0:34:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this has to do with the nature of the mind,\Nand it has to do with meditation and contemplation.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.48,0:34:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The first thing we notice about the reality of the mind\Nis that 98% of the mind is silent at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.53,0:34:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,People say,\NI meditate and I can't get the mind to quiet down
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.53,0:34:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and the reality is that about actually more than 98%,\N99% of the mind is silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.38,0:34:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Only 1% of your mind is actually talking,\Ncreating words and images and sequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.38,0:34:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, right prior to thought,\Nright prior to thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.69,0:34:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,your mind is silent right now.\NThe mind of everybody in this room is silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.05,0:35:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the silence arises a thought.\NWhere does the thought come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.26,0:35:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes out of silence.\NPrior to the thought, there is silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.26,0:35:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,People think, you know,\Nin terms of the Newtonian paradigm of reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.73,0:35:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,which calibrates in the mid-400s,\Nthe Newtonian paradigm of reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.73,0:35:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is about 450 or 460,\Nwhich is intelligent,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.67,0:35:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but not staggering genius either.\NThe idea of causality is that based on this dualistic system,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.73,0:35:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,which creates a this and a that,\Nthe belief in duality then is probably the main block to enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.17,0:35:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The main block to enlightenment\Nis the common human belief in duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.48,0:36:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,America, the calibrated level of consciousness of America right now\Nis about 421,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.96,0:36:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,which is actually the highest in the world,\Nhighest living country in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.15,0:36:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody comes near 421.\NSo the intellect then in the 400s,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.88,0:36:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is the world of science.\N400 is extremely high.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.38,0:36:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The 400s are extremely high.\NOut of it comes science.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.61,0:36:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of it comes all the wonders of the modern world.\NAntibiotics, cure of diseases,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.38,0:36:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,microscopes, telescopes,\Ngoing off into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.82,0:36:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All the wonders of the modern world.\NWhat we stand on here was manufactured in some factory.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.92,0:36:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All these dyes all comes out of the chemical industry.\NThe productivity,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.34,0:36:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of the U.S.,\Nof course,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.46,0:36:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is the enormous benefit of invention,\Nmagnified through science,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.46,0:37:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and industrialized as productivity.\NAnd it provides the highest standard of living in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.73,0:37:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The lowest death rate,\Nthe lowest infant mortality rate,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.01,0:37:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the longest lifespan.\NIn my lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.73,0:37:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the average lifespan has jumped to about 20 years.\NUsually you retired at 65,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.86,0:37:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you toured the country,\Nand then had a heart attack,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.86,0:37:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and you left.\NYou would have went to live with your kids,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.86,0:37:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and that was the story.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.36,0:37:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So the great benefit of the 400s, then,\Nis the world of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.36,0:37:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The world of science.\NThe intellect, however,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.51,0:37:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes the great barrier.\NAs we said,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.78,0:37:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,only 4% transcend level 500.\NVery few people get beyond 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.09,0:37:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein was 499.\NSir Isaac Newton was 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.09,0:37:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud was 499.\NFor the great submerged people of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.42,0:38:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,third world or whatever they call them,\N400 is way, way beyond them.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.84,0:38:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The intellect and reason\Nwith which we approach other countries
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.13,0:38:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is foolhardy.\NThey have the slightest interest in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.13,0:38:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're starving to death,\Nwho cares about political philosophy
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.46,0:38:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,like democracy and equality?\NGive me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.46,0:38:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My kids are starving.\NI want to know what's going to feed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.07,0:38:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Get real.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.13,0:38:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So the intellect is blind\Nto its own limitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.01,0:38:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Science, you know,\Nscience and consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.01,0:38:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,conferences,\Nthere's another one coming up soon,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.01,0:38:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,someplace or other.\NThey all calibrate about,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.01,0:38:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,well, the next one coming up\Ncalibrates only 420.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.01,0:38:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of them usually calibrate around 450.\NSo although science is aware
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.01,0:38:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's limited,\Nit goes to advanced theoretical physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.09,0:38:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,it goes to quantum mechanics,\Nand there it stops.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.09,0:39:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes to nonlinear dynamics,\Nbut it draws back,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.13,0:39:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,because at that jump,\Nyou have to make the Heisenberg leap,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.13,0:39:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and you have to realize\Nthat you have to shift the subjectivity
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.15,0:39:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,because intentionality determines\Nwhat you will discover.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.15,0:39:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The Heisenberg principle\Nis witnessed in everyday life.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.15,0:39:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What you believe in,\Nwhat you seek,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.15,0:39:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,what you intend\Nis what you discover.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.15,0:39:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That then verifies your intention,\Nand that's why the ego is so powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.26,0:39:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Because first of all,\Nit decides in advance
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.26,0:39:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,what it's going to find.\NIt then finds it and says,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.26,0:39:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,see, I told you.\NIt becomes, therefore, self-limiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.69,0:39:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The way out is by the Heisenberg principle,\Nwhich we'll get to later.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.69,0:39:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But Einstein himself drew back\Nat the quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.69,0:39:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,at the level of 490 sun 9,\Nand as I've told you before,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.69,0:40:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein said,\NI prefer to believe
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.23,0:40:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that there's an objective,\Nself-existent universe out there
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.23,0:40:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,independent of consciousness.\NSo he drew back at that paradigm jump
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.23,0:40:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because you can't understand consciousness\Nunless you jump to the 500s
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.23,0:40:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because consciousness\Nis absolute subjectivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.23,0:40:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Subjectivity.\NWell, we'll go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.28,0:40:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we're going to explain\Nhow the mind works.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.28,0:40:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So the mind is like a silent,\Nand about one or two percent of it
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.28,0:40:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is creating thoughts\Nout of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.28,0:40:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,To understand that,\Nthen we have to transcend
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.78,0:40:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian paradigm\Nof reality of causality,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.78,0:40:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,which sees thoughts as a stream\Nin which the thought on the left
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.78,0:40:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is creating the thought on the right,\Nsort of like reading across the page.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.78,0:40:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It thinks that creation\Nis a linear phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.09,0:40:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of a this doing a that.\NThat becomes the great block
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.84,0:41:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to enlightenment\Nbecause enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.84,0:41:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is the elimination of the illusion\Nthat there's a separate I
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.84,0:41:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the secret thinker,\Nthe secret doer
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.84,0:41:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that is the causer of anything.\NAnd when you transcend that,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.86,0:41:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you see that everything is happening\Nspontaneously of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.86,0:41:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't any you doing anything.\NIt's all happening of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.15,0:41:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo how do phenomena come about then
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.11,0:41:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,if it is not a process,\Nif they're not the consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.11,0:41:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of causality\Nand a sequence of linear causes?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.44,0:41:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Because reality is nonlinear.\NIt's describable
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.44,0:41:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,from a linear viewpoint,\Nbut that's only a viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.44,0:41:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not a reality.\NYou can choose to describe it
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.44,0:41:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,from any viewpoint you wish.\NNewtonian linear is one
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.44,0:41:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that's productive\Nin the physical world.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.44,0:42:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it is a limitation.\NSo we'll recapitulate
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.82,0:42:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,what we said in previous lectures\Nabout how phenomena come about.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.82,0:42:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The way phenomena come about\Nis within the Newtonian
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.61,0:42:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,describable paradigm there is\Nthat which is definable,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.57,0:42:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and it has to do with form.\NForm exists, however.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.73,0:42:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It has a contingency\Nupon an energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.73,0:42:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,which is influencing it\Ncalled local conditions,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.73,0:42:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,local conditions.\NThen beyond that
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.42,0:42:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is an infinite field\Nof infinite power,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.42,0:42:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness itself\Nbeyond time, temporality, dimension,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.42,0:42:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond here, now, there,\Ncompletely nonlinear,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.82,0:42:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but infinitely power, powerful.\NSo force, force,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.51,0:42:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrating below 200,\Nforce is the world of form,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.51,0:43:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian paradigm reality.\NForce goes from here to there.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.71,0:43:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In doing that, it consumes energy,\Nand in doing that,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.78,0:43:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it creates counterforce.\NThe reason force is limited
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.98,0:43:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and eventually fails\Nis because you have to feed
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.98,0:43:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it enormous energy,\Neventually feeding
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.98,0:43:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the Roman legions\Nall across half the globe.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.01,0:43:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They couldn't do it anymore.\NSo force requires energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.65,0:43:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and you have to constantly\Npour energy into it
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.65,0:43:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in the form of money,\Nlives of soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.65,0:43:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to keep more troops\Ngoing in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.65,0:43:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They shoot them down,\Nmore troops, more troops,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.65,0:43:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,more munitions, more food for them,\Nmore clothes for them,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.65,0:43:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,more taxes from the people,\Nmore using up the resources
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.86,0:43:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of the country, more mining,\Npulling up all the resources,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.86,0:43:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,throwing it into the war machine.\NEventually, you just fall down exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.96,0:43:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In the meantime,\Nusing force creates counterforce.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.96,0:43:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you haven't noticed,\Nthe minute you shoot,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.96,0:43:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody will shoot back at you.\NSo the same phenomenon
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.96,0:44:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,goes on both sides.\NFinally, they run out of young men,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.96,0:44:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,they run out of money,\Nand they collapse.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.46,0:44:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Power, on the other hand,\Nis more like gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.03,0:44:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Power just stands there.\NPower just is.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.57,0:44:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And as a consequence\Nof the quality of that which it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.73,0:44:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it uplifts all within it.\NIt influences.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.86,0:44:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the giant electromagnetic field\Nin which the little iron filings
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.92,0:44:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,called you and I,\Nwhose configuration is karmically determined
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.30,0:44:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,with little wiggle waggles here.\NSo now within the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.30,0:44:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you automatically gravitate to this\Nas a consequence of the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.30,0:44:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,not caused by anything.\NNothing is causing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.69,0:44:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,To say the field is causing it\Nis an error of logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.69,0:45:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an intellectualization\Nyou project onto it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.42,0:45:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is causing anything.\NYou can witness the phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.42,0:45:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,To conjecture some operative principle\Nis already a mentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.03,0:45:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The field, which is infinite,\Nbeyond definition,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.44,0:45:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and only experienced subjectively,\Nand when it's experienced subjectively,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.63,0:45:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the phenomena has been the same\Nthroughout all of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.11,0:45:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,7,000 B.C. in the Aryan culture\Nof ancient India.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.11,0:45:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The great sages became enlightened\Nand out of that we have Vedanta,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.26,0:45:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the Rig Veda,\Nthe Upanishads,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.80,0:45:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the great spiritual geniuses\Nof all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.80,0:45:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We're the first ones to let go of the ego\Nand experience the infinite reality
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.86,0:46:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which all existence arises.\NZoroaster was another great avatar.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.32,0:46:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So the great avatars calibrated 1,000.\NOne is the level of the bacteria,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.92,0:46:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the first conscious life.\N1,000 is as far as the human nervous system can go.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.92,0:46:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,As a matter of fact,\Nthe human nervous system can really only go
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.15,0:46:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,comfortably up to 700.\NOne out of 10 million ever reaches 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.26,0:46:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hardly anybody goes beyond 700.\NOnly a few in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.86,0:46:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus the Christ calibrated 1,000.\NBuddha calibrated 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.57,0:46:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Muhammad calibrated 740\Nat the time he dictated the Quran.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.07,0:46:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The Quran is at 700.\NAnd then at age 35,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.42,0:46:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Muhammad crashed,\Nwent from 700 down to 135,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.65,0:47:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,took up the sword\Nand began killing infidels,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.65,0:47:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,which has gone on for 1,400 years now.\NA lot of infidels left.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.11,0:47:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Blow up 3,000,\Nyou only got 300 million more Americans to go
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.90,0:47:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,before you can finally get them all.\NThough the downside of it
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.96,0:47:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is that explosive nature.\NAt the lower levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.42,0:47:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Phenomena then happen by virtue\Nof their potentiality becoming an actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.50,0:47:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The unmanifest becomes manifest.\NWithin the power of this field,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.09,0:47:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the potential of this seed\Nbecomes the flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.46,0:47:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the field,\Nthe seed does not become a flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.46,0:47:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It rots.\NIt has not within it
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.76,0:48:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of creation.\NNothing has within it
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.76,0:48:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the power to create its own existence.\NExistence comes out of
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.96,0:48:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the infinite power of the field.\NAs you transcend the 400s then,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.63,0:48:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to witness\Nthe phenomena are happening of their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.55,0:48:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,To that point,\Nyou have the illusion there is a me
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.55,0:48:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,causing it to do that.\NUntil one day,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.82,0:48:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,things happen\Nand you realize
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.82,0:48:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it happened\Non its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.82,0:48:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you begin to realize\Neverything is happening
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.73,0:48:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,on its own.\NEven deliberate planning
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.90,0:48:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is spontaneously happening\Non its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.90,0:48:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo this 1% of talkingness
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.51,0:48:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is an addiction.\NWe're going to do a lecture
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.17,0:48:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,just on how to transcend that\Nin Sedona.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.17,0:48:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I think early next year.\NBut,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.46,0:49:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,one,\Nin deep meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.30,0:49:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you will witness\Nthat thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.86,0:49:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of an energy field\Ndevoted to thinkingness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.96,0:49:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's coming out of an intentionality\Nand as you surrender it,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.96,0:49:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind stops.\N98% of the mind is silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.71,0:49:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Only 1% is talking.\NBut we focus on that 1%.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.07,0:49:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nalthough 98% of the mind is silent,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.13,0:49:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,we become hypnotized by the 1%.\NWe become entrapped by it,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.13,0:49:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,entranced by it,\Nentranced by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.13,0:49:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And how does the 1%\Nkeep you in a hypnotic state?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.13,0:49:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The thinking that's going on\Nin your mind
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.46,0:49:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is a hypnotic phenomena.\NLet's ask that.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.46,0:49:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my right arm.\NIn case you didn't know,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.46,0:49:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Susan was my right arm.\NYou all know by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.46,0:49:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The activity of the mind\Nis a hypnotic phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.46,0:50:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Hypnotic phenomena.\NWhich one is hypnotized
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.01,0:50:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,by the 1%?\N1% of the mind is talking
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.13,0:50:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're in a hypnotic state.\NIsn't that scary?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.63,0:50:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,How does the 1% keep its hold over you?\NIt politicizes everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.09,0:50:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,God help me with my politicization.\NI don't want to hear
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.09,0:50:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,whether God's a he or a she.\NGive me a break, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.09,0:50:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,God's beyond gender.\NOh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.38,0:50:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It moralizes, it idealizes,\Nit hypothesizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.51,0:50:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the action, man.\NRomanticizing, criticizing, emotionalizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.51,0:50:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Dramatizing, catastrophizing, theorizing.\NRationalizes, fantasizes,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.73,0:50:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,fanalizes, intellectualizes,\Nmentalizes, idealizes,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.73,0:50:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,glamorizes, demonizes,\Nparasitizes, victimizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.73,0:50:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy.\NNo wonder we have to sleep at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.13,0:50:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we get hypnotized by it?\NIt's seductive.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.19,0:51:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The seduction of the media\Nis going on in your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.69,0:51:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason the media\Nhas so much power over you
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.69,0:51:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is because you are already\Nin a hypnotic state.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.73,0:51:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in a hypnotic state.\NYou're in a hypnotic state.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.73,0:51:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Seduced by the glamorization\Nof form and ideation, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.73,0:51:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, you would find TV ultra-boring.\NWhen I first left the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.13,0:51:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I never watched TV for 10 or 20 years.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.13,0:51:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I never read a newspaper or a magazine.\NJust gave up the world of glamorized informationism.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.13,0:51:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Informationism.\NIt informationizes everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.65,0:51:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean you haven't heard?\NI didn't know Regan was shot
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.65,0:51:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,until, I don't know, a month later.\NRegan was shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.65,0:51:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, you don't say.\NGo on, next.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.65,0:51:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NOh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.73,0:51:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we mentioned quantum mechanics,\Nyou see,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.21,0:52:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because we need another slide\Nthat comes later
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.21,0:52:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to show how this all works.\NHere we got a whiteboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.32,0:52:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.\NWe'll do it here
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.32,0:52:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it'll show up later\Non the slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.32,0:52:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We said,\Nhere's the Newtonian.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.32,0:52:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if this is up high enough\Nfor you guys to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.32,0:52:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think so.\NWe can put it up on the stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.32,0:52:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do this.\NHere.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.32,0:52:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll bring it up on the stage.\NI'll take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.61,0:52:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring it up on the stage.\NI'll take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.67,0:52:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take this.\NI'll take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.67,0:52:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take this.\NI'll take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.92,0:52:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring it up on the stage.\NI think it's going to come up later
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.28,0:52:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,on the slide anyway,\Nbut just to explain
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.28,0:52:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,what we're talking about.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.92,0:52:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.88,0:52:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's great.\NThank you much.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.67,0:52:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the world of form.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.67,0:52:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You can measure it,\Nweigh it,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.67,0:52:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,drill it,\Npaint it,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.73,0:52:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,count it,\Nsell it,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.73,0:52:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,kill people with it,\Nall kinds of useful things.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.53,0:52:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Its use is now\Nunder the influence
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.57,0:52:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of a proximate field.\NThis is the coaxial field.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.38,0:52:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the coaxial field.\NThis is the coaxial field.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.38,0:52:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the coaxial field.\NThis is the coaxial field.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.38,0:53:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the coaxial field.\NThis is the coaxial field.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.78,0:53:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the content of the field.\NThis is the world of science
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.78,0:53:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,defined.\NSo the mechanistic reductionist said,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.78,0:53:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing is real\Nunless we can weigh it,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.78,0:53:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,drill it,\Npaint it,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.98,0:53:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,measure it,\Nfind it in time and space.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.98,0:53:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a very limited paradigm of reality.\NAnd he says that,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.46,0:53:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and he believes it,\Nbut of course it's not a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.46,0:53:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And frankly he doesn't believe it\Nbecause it's from subjectivity
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.46,0:53:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,he's making this great announcement.\NIt's only real if I can measure it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.46,0:53:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NWhat happens
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.67,0:53:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens in the world of form, the Newtonian paradigm, then, is due to the influence of proximate, proximate field.\NSo this is the proximate field.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.67,0:53:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This only happens if certain things are going on in the proximate field.\NTo measure it, you've got to have a ruler. You've got to be able to count.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.15,0:54:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to be there. It requires a human being.\NA lot of phenomena are required, so you have to have a concordance, then, of conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.28,0:54:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The flower doesn't bloom unless it has water, sunshine, various other things.\NThis is the content of the field, content of the field, people who live in lower minds.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.11,0:54:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,See, mind has two levels, two different etheric brains, really, lower mind and higher mind.\NLower mind is pedestrian, limited, unimaginative. It lives in this extremely boring world.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.09,0:54:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The way it appears and the way it behaves is then due to many influences.\NPublic opinion, persuasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.09,0:54:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The impact of a television commercial depends on the arrangement of the figures,\Nwhether you've got a movie star, the background music, the color.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.21,0:54:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the condition about it, then, automatically has a consequence.\NAnd that's the way karma works.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.46,0:55:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We all gravitate to that which we are perfectly aligned with and concordant with.\NAnd a thing we recently verified was the exact conditions of one's birth,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.38,0:55:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,time, place, parents, etc., is karmically perfect.\NYou want to verify that?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.61,0:55:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything about your birth is karmically perfect.\NIt's this, karmically perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.55,0:55:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Where you're at this moment is karmically perfect.\NKarmically perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.78,0:55:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The world goes from perfection to perfection to perfection.\NPerfection to perfection to perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.01,0:55:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is perfectly perfect.\NCompletely and completely, it's potentiality at every second.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.17,0:56:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,At this second, the half-unfolded rose is 100% of all it can be at this moment.\NThe same thing happens in the next instant, the next instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.92,0:56:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the pan is perfectly moving across the field of vision.\NIt's perfectly what it is at every moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.15,0:56:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Life moves from perfection to perfection.\NThat's enough to blow me away just thinking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.34,0:56:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we're very fuzzy today.\NMaybe we'll move this over more to the right, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.55,0:56:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we should, maybe there's a smudge on this thing here.\NNo?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.17,0:56:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so here's the world of science, logic, rationality.\NEverything is seen as separate.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.17,0:56:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's reductionistic.\NIt's literal, pedestrian.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.17,0:56:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is deterministic.\NEverything is settled.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.17,0:56:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way it is.\NEverything is limited.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.90,0:56:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's definable.\NIt's constricted.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.90,0:56:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's finished.\NIt's certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.90,0:57:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's the world of force.\NAll right, now move it a little bit more to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.03,0:57:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We move beyond that, see?\NBecause the next field, yeah, this is the Newtonian field.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.03,0:57:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,As you begin to get out of the Newtonian field,\Nyou begin to enter the world of nonlinear dynamics
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.03,0:57:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and the quantum potentialities and realities that are possible.\NSo the quantum dimension now,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.09,0:57:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in which intention and Heisenberg principle determines\Nthat you go from the Dirac equations,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.34,0:57:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the description of the way the world is now,\Nthen by intention and decision and observation,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.44,0:57:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you collapse the wave function,\Nand you now go from the Schrodinger equations,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.44,0:57:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Schrodinger equations,\Nvia the Heisenberg process.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.82,0:58:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Potentiality becomes an actuality.\NThe universe has changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.36,0:58:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You collapse the wave function of the potentiality\Nas established by the Schrodinger equations,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.65,0:58:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,both time-dependent and time-independent,\Nthrough the Heisenberg principle then.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.88,0:58:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,By intention and by decision, you collapse the wave function.\NNow you have a new universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.88,0:58:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The state of the universe has changed,\Ncalibratable via the Dirac equations,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.13,0:58:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,through the phenomenon process, process one.\NDecision then collapses it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.55,0:58:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the new quantum mechanics,\Nyou begin to see the world is movable,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.94,0:58:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,freely, it's creative, it's imaginative.\NThings are not discrete.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.03,0:58:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not minimal, they're diffuse.\NEverything is involved in everything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.19,0:58:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You get a feeling of the holographic universe.\NThings are observable but not provable.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.38,0:58:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Not provable.\NThings are simultaneous.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.71,0:59:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not sequential.\NEverything has potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.71,0:59:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the equations we were talking about before.\NIt's called stochastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.78,0:59:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Stochastic because out of the linear arises the nonlinear.\N19 times bitten by a rattlesnake.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.42,0:59:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Guy in Sedona.\NUsed to go out and get rattlesnakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.42,0:59:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Call him up.\NWe got a rattlesnake.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.65,0:59:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He and his partner run over and get him.\NI never realized what he did with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.92,0:59:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Not my business.\NMight have ate him.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.28,0:59:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what he did with him.\NAnyway, he got bitten 19 times,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.76,0:59:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and the 20th time the rattlesnake bite killed him.\NGood as a mackerel.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.76,0:59:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In a matter of seconds.\NThat's why I'm not a fan of extreme sports,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.90,0:59:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,because you can do that high jump 18 times, 19th time.\NJust as you go off, somebody says,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.90,1:00:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,did you send your mother a Christmas card?\NAnd now you can spend your life in a wheelchair.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.03,1:00:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Wheelchair.\NParalyzed from the neck down.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.15,1:00:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm not an enthusiast about extreme sports\Nbecause I'm aware of nonlinear dynamics.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.15,1:00:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And I know that sooner or later,\Nit's based on the scientific principle of iteration.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.15,1:00:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,One digit out in the 26th decimal repeated enough times\Nis enough to throw you so far off
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.76,1:00:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that you won't be even on the same racetrack.\NYou'll be on a different racetrack.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.76,1:00:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is not limited.\NIt is not predictable.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.13,1:00:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nonlinear.\NOut of a thousand generations of black beetles,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.15,1:00:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,wham, an albino.\NOkay, so unlimited, stochastic, altered by observation.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.28,1:00:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's expansive.\NAnd it's subjective.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.28,1:00:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the world of power,\Nwhereas the world of the Newtonian paradigm is force.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.28,1:01:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Force creating counter-force.\NMeasurable, exhaustible.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.28,1:01:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NNext one, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.65,1:01:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWell, I don't know why this is here.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.69,1:01:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We just want to, oh yes,\Nconfirm the reality of God, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.69,1:01:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,God has been a discussion for a long time, you see.\NAnyway, we thought, just for the fun of it,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.36,1:01:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,we would calibrate all the levels of divinity\Nand the denotations of divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.36,1:01:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and higher levels of consciousness.\NThe scale of consciousness goes up to 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.36,1:01:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And then people ask, what's over 600?\NAnd as I say, it refers to extremely few people.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.17,1:01:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So I didn't think it was all that interesting,\Nbut people were.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.17,1:01:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So we went from 600 up to 1,000.\NYou see, 1,000 is the capacity,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.17,1:01:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the maximum capacity of the human nervous system.\NIn fact, it's only comfortable up to about 700,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.26,1:02:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,over 700.\NIt is very uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.26,1:02:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And one is often wracked with pains\Nand excruciating things
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.55,1:02:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,because the nervous system then begins to actually increase.\NIt adds protein to the nerves.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.55,1:02:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And to go beyond 700,\Nyou have to alter the nervous system,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.55,1:02:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which takes some years.\NAnd so for some years, one goes through various agonies
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.55,1:02:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,described by the Buddha and others.\NSo enlightenment is 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.96,1:02:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we went, the sage, teacher of enlightenment,\Nthe avatar, we said, is 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.96,1:02:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ, Buddha, Krishna, Brahma, Zora, Esther.\NAnd what is beyond 1,000?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.92,1:02:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Archangels calibrate 50,000 and over.\NAnd the great avatar, the realities that we defer to as God,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.19,1:03:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate as infinite.\NThe field of consciousness itself is infinite.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.30,1:03:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond time, beyond dimension.\NAnd as one goes into that state where the mind becomes silent,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.44,1:03:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the reality that you've always been is stunning.\NThat which you are has always been, will always be.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.69,1:03:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's not possible to be otherwise\Nor it couldn't exist in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.69,1:03:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's hard to see.\NYeah, next.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.69,1:03:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What?\NOh, this is the distribution of levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.40,1:03:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,around the world.\NWe talked about this last night.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.80,1:03:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We said, people say, what is the world\Nand what is the purpose of human life in this world?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.09,1:03:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We think we're very advanced.\NNobody knows where we came from, why we're here,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.25,1:03:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,or where we're going.\NYou call that advanced?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.25,1:04:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's not out of kindergarten.\NWho are we?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.59,1:04:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are we here?\NHow do we get here?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.59,1:04:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And where are we going?\NWe're going to colonize other planets.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.48,1:04:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right.\NThey've been sending me messages.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.48,1:04:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You can get it in my e-mail.\NPlease, please don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.48,1:04:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't.\NPlease do not populate our planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.48,1:04:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got enough problems with a lot of humans landing here.\NConsciousness evolves over great eons of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.92,1:04:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness preceded life on this planet.\NIt was an a priori as a quality of divinity itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.40,1:04:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness evolved over a great millennium of time.\NIt then seeded itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.09,1:05:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It seeded itself on this planet and evolved.\NSo what is life on this planet?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.13,1:05:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Life on this planet, then, is like a temporary staging area.\NConsciousness, when you go into a higher state
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.11,1:05:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see how long your consciousness has existed,\Nhistory books are like a joke beyond the oldest Buddha that ever was.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.82,1:05:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I was already.\NSo the soul and its migratory evolution, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.67,1:05:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,temporarily lands here in this staging area.\NFrom here, it has choices with karmic consequences
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.67,1:05:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,which influence its destination.\NThis is not the ultimate destination.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.44,1:05:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Earth is neither at the beginning nor is it the end,\Nbut a staging area.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.05,1:06:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So last night we likened it to an island in the middle of the Pacific,\Nand the migrating birds come, all different kinds of birds,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.05,1:06:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,from different places,\Nand they land in this staging area.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.05,1:06:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And when the times and the conditions are right,\Nthey take off to their ultimate destinations.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.30,1:06:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The island is not the origination nor is it the finalization.\NIt's a staging area.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.53,1:06:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Human life is a staging area\Nin which the karmic propensities of the spirit as it comes in
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.53,1:06:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,are already preset, already set.\NEverybody already has a calibratable level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.34,1:06:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,at the moment of birth.\NThe moment of birth, you're already born
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.34,1:06:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,with a specific level of consciousness.\NIt's so profound an understanding.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.44,1:06:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the truth.\NEverybody already has a calibratable level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.44,1:07:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the minute you're here.\NSo unless consciousness preceded the appearance here on Earth as a human,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.59,1:07:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,how would you account for the fact everybody's got a different one?\NEverybody has a different level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.46,1:07:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So consciousness evolves,\Nand then when it's propitious, it incarnates.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.26,1:07:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,When consciousness incarnates,\Nit tends to do like the birds would do.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.15,1:07:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All the little pelican-types go land on this part of the island,\Nand the wicky-wocky birds land over here.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.34,1:07:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, here you see the wicky-wocky birds,\Nhow they land on an island,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.34,1:07:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the island called the planet.\NHere you got 421 is up in this area,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.63,1:07:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,up in Greenland we got 350.\NMost of Central America is 300s.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.73,1:07:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all 300s.\NYou don't expect big trouble from these people.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.40,1:07:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,People in the 300s are rational.\NI mean, you know, they're intelligent.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.40,1:07:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They've got motivation.\NThey might have lived their life already.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.40,1:08:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In the middle of that, out of this whole Western hemisphere,\NI don't see any trouble arising anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.40,1:08:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you've got an isolated community.\NHere it calibrates at 55.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.40,1:08:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not going to cause any trouble\Nbecause at 55 you ain't got the what's
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.98,1:08:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to cause trouble to anybody.\NYou're lucky if you can stay alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.73,1:08:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAll right, we'll move on to the other side.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.34,1:08:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They're into esoteric practices\Nto keep their consciousness where it is,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.34,1:08:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, voodoo and stuff.\NAll right, demonic.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.35,1:08:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, 410, you see Australia is in great shape.\NYou see China, 300s,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.69,1:08:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Mongolia, 175.\NYou see most of the area, India, 355.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.69,1:08:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So certain parts of the world,\Nyou're not going to expect any trouble.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.96,1:08:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you've got the 200s.\NEurope, you're running into the 300s.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.96,1:08:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is Europe?\NI don't know where it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.96,1:08:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, here.\NIn Europe, you're running around the 300s.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.96,1:09:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,England, Ireland, France, Ireland, around in there.\NPeople in the 300s make political mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.55,1:09:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They get taken over by megalomaniacs,\Nbut they themselves, left to their own devices,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.55,1:09:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,are pretty reasonable.\NThe main problem is the same place
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.55,1:09:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that Time magazine denoted\Nas problem areas of life is North Africa.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.55,1:09:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you're running a 180 against a 190,\Nwith both below 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.55,1:09:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,which is pride, arrogance,\Nand then you fall down even lower.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.57,1:09:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You get down as far as 40,\Nwhich is way down in the spleen.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.57,1:09:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You just conquer people next door\Nbecause you like to slaughter them, you know, mainly.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.57,1:09:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So you get extremely low levels of consciousness.\NThese people are not threats to the world
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.57,1:09:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,because they don't have enough power,\Nbut they kill each other routinely.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.57,1:09:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They kill each other.\NThey never capture anybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.57,1:09:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They always massacre them, you know.\NThey haven't even gotten up to slavery.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.57,1:09:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize slavery is a step up\Nfrom massacring people?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.26,1:09:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It took the Vikings quite a while.\NThey massacred thousands and thousands.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.78,1:10:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, man, we can get money for these creatures.\NUh-oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.78,1:10:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They stopped slaughtering them and started to sell them.\NThat was an improvement
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.78,1:10:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,from slaughtering people\Nto keeping them alive and feeding them
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.72,1:10:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because now they're a commodity.\NSo slavery was a commodity of West Africa.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.72,1:10:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a worldwide commodity.\NSlavery was endemic to mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.85,1:10:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,In the days of ancient Rome,\N9 out of 10 people were slaves.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.97,1:10:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Only 1 out of 10 were citizens of Rome.\N90% of the people,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.97,1:10:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,including the scientists, the surgeons,\Nthe most educated people were all slaves.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.55,1:10:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It only recently has come to a collapse.\NAll right, so you would expect trouble then.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.53,1:10:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't expect trouble from the world here\Nbecause they don't have enough power.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.53,1:10:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But at 180 to 190,\Nyou get two countries warring.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.53,1:10:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,For thousands of years,\N180 against 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.53,1:10:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,One side throws rocks.\NThe other one shoots back.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.53,1:11:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Then this one bombs this one.\NAnd bombing a busload of children is the best.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.53,1:11:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the best.\NThat's sure to induce hate
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.53,1:11:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and keep the war going a long time,\Nwhich is very profitable.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.53,1:11:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Diminishing industries in these countries,\Nit's very profitable.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.98,1:11:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,No likelihood of diminution.\NNo, we saw that already.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.98,1:11:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.43,1:11:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I missed one.\NWhat's that one?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.46,1:11:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this is more advanced stuff\Nwhere you begin to realize
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.57,1:11:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that the levels of consciousness\Nhave to do with progressive detachment from content.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.69,1:11:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NHere people identify with the content.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.27,1:11:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Here they identify with the form.\NHere they realize that they're only talking about an observation.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.65,1:12:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You're only talking about an observation.\NThe difficulty with the intellect and the mind
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.85,1:12:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is it doesn't know res cogitans from res externa.\NIt doesn't know which belongs to the field of mentation
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.92,1:12:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and which is in the world.\NAnd it thinks if I can mentalize it,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.02,1:12:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,it must be that way out there.\NOne of the great defects of reason,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.61,1:12:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,pointed out first by Descartes.\NConfusion of res cogitans,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.61,1:12:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is of the mind,\Nwith res externa,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.81,1:12:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is the world.\NThe world exists independent
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.97,1:12:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of what your thoughts are about it.\NOccasionally the two are in accord with each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.10,1:12:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So you begin to withdraw\Nand you realize that you are not the subject of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.17,1:13:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not the me that you think is going on there.\NInstead, as you meditate,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.17,1:13:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to realize that you're the witness of the mind.\NYou're not the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.30,1:13:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If you were the mind,\Nyou wouldn't know what the mind was thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.30,1:13:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Something has to be removed to the mind\Nin order to witness it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.32,1:13:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And you realize that you're the witness,\Nthe watcher of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.32,1:13:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And many spiritual teachers,\Nsuch as Nisargadatta Maharaj,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.32,1:13:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,would recommend to their students,\Njust watch the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.32,1:13:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Do nothing else.\NJust go and spend a couple years
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.32,1:13:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,watching the mind and come back.\NAnd in just watching and witnessing the mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.77,1:13:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,it stops identifying with it.\NIt stops identifying with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.77,1:13:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And you begin to realize\Nyou're the witness of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.77,1:13:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the idea that there is a you\Nthat is witnessing the mind disappears
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.15,1:13:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and one realizes that witnessing\Nis a phenomena that's impersonal.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.80,1:13:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind is witnessing itself,\Nwitnessing itself as an aspect of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.22,1:14:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And you begin to see that you are the witness.\NAnd then you see the impersonality
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.78,1:14:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness itself.\NThat what's going on is what you think is you
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.78,1:14:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is really nothing but consciousness\Nwitnessing a screenplay out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.78,1:14:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And you eventually transcend\Nthe identification of self with mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.85,1:14:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So the first step in advancing consciousness\Nis to realize that I am not the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.85,1:14:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If you lose your arm, you're still you.\NYou lose another arm, you're still you.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.21,1:14:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You can lose everything and you're still you.\NThe sense of me, I-ness,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.21,1:14:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't have to do with the physicality.\NYou then stop identifying yourself as mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.01,1:14:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You transcend mind even as witness.\NYou realize that you're not even the witnessing of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.19,1:14:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Witnessing of the mind is going on of its own.\NNobody here is deciding
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.19,1:14:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to be aware of what your mind is doing.\NIt's happening of its own.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.19,1:14:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The witnessing, the consciousness\Nof the content of the mind
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.77,1:15:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is an automatic phenomena.\NIt's not you, it's automatic.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.77,1:15:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If it was you, you could stop it.\NTry to stop being aware
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.77,1:15:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of what your mind is doing or thinking.\NYou see, it's not you.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.77,1:15:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If it was you, you could stop it any time you want.\NYou say, mind, stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.77,1:15:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't do that.\NThose are the steps to enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.81,1:15:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move beyond that because\Nyou've got to watch the time this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.15,1:15:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What time are we going to take a break?\NTwelve?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.38,1:15:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\NOkay, hurry up.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.38,1:15:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got all the way to enlightenment by noon.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.39,1:15:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we want to see the top first.\NThe reason the world doesn't have peace
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.93,1:15:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is it doesn't know what peace is.\NIt doesn't know what the cause of war is.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.93,1:15:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If it, first of all, doesn't know what truth is,\Nso how could it have peace or prevent war?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.93,1:15:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace is the automatic state of affairs\Nwhen truth prevails.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.97,1:16:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,When truth prevails, peace is automatic.\NIt's natural.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.57,1:16:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a quality of truth.\NRadiates forth as peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.67,1:16:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Its absence is called falsehood.\NSo, because this is fuzzy and you can't read it,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.36,1:16:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll move it down a little bit.\NPeace is the natural state when truth prevails.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.55,1:16:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,War is the state when falsehood prevails.\NThe basis of war is ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.89,1:16:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't any other cause of ignorance.\NWhat is the ignorance?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.93,1:16:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The human mind cannot discern truth from falsehood.\NConsequently, it's unable to discern
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.22,1:16:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,a true leader from a megalomaniac.\NYou have to be very sophisticated
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.73,1:16:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to know their difference.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.60,1:16:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Because some megalomaniacs start out integrists.\NNapoleon and Hitler
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.60,1:16:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,started being two obvious examples.\NBoth Napoleon and Hitler did great things for their countries,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.67,1:17:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and they both calibrated about 450 to 460 at that time.\NThen, you know, like power corrupts
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.46,1:17:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and absolute power corrupts absolutely,\Nmegalomaniacs set in,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.68,1:17:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see their calibrated level of consciousness\Nwent from 450, which is integrists, intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.68,1:17:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Napoleon did great things for France,\Nand Hitler did great things for Germany.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.77,1:17:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But then the power gets to them.\NThe egocentric, narcissistic megalomania of the ego takes over.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.22,1:17:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see that Napoleon dropped from 440 or something\Nto the time of the Battle of Waterloo.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.57,1:17:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The Duke of Wellington calibrated like 440 or 450,\Nsomething like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.27,1:17:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And at that time, Napoleon calibrated like,\NI forget, 90 or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.27,1:17:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The same thing happened with Adolf Hitler.\NIn the beginning, he calibrated high.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.50,1:18:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, of course, he collapsed,\Nand I forget what he calibrated when he went down in flames.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.46,1:18:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So even if you're like Milosevic,\Nyou can't even, you know, the populace can't tell a leader
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.44,1:18:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,from a megalomaniac,\Nmuch less the subtlety that was once an integrist leader
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.44,1:18:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,has become a megalomaniac.\NThat's even more subtle yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.44,1:18:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Frankly, nobody gets it,\Nexcept the German high command.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.51,1:18:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,God, that Hitler is becoming megalomaniac.\NYou can go back in time and calibrate exactly what time
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.51,1:18:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and what circumstances.\NI think with Napoleon, it was when he crowned himself emperor.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.51,1:18:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,See, before that time, the Pope crowned heads of Europe.\NNapoleon put the crown on his own head
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.14,1:18:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and usurped the power of God as reflected symbolically\Nthrough the Christhood,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.60,1:18:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,transmitted authoritatively through the papacy.\NAnd when he crowned himself emperor,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.36,1:19:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's when it happened, yeah?\NLet's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.36,1:19:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Napoleon, we have permission to ask this, resist.\NNapoleon crashed when he crowned himself emperor.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.72,1:19:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NYeah, so here is 450,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.03,1:19:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and suddenly the power, the adulation and the power\Nbegins to get like a disease, feeds his ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.03,1:19:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of going into humility,\Nso what saves the great conqueror?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.30,1:19:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What saves the great conqueror from megalomania is humility.\NTo thee, O God, do I.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.51,1:19:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my victories.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.46,1:19:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So the inability to tell,\Nshe keeps whipping the truth away from us.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.64,1:19:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The human mind is unable to discern truth from falsehood.\NTherefore, it cannot tell a leader from a megalomaniac.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.89,1:20:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego gets programmed into polarized ego positions,\Nwhich comprises about 50% of what's on the Internet right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.89,1:20:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It ends up as a distortion of truth and propaganda.\NThe consequence to mankind is death and destruction.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.26,1:20:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In my lifetime, 100 million people slaughtered.\N100 million people were slaughtered by what?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.11,1:20:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,By the inability to tell truth from falsehood.\NThat's it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.11,1:20:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The inability to tell truth from falsehood allows that which is fallacious\Nto gain power in the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.78,1:20:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and young people become gun fodder.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.23,1:20:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll just do calibrations on World War II.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.23,1:20:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrations on World War II, because it's illustrative,\Nand we've got two more minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.34,1:20:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Friday night, I was telling the people I was reminiscing about\Nwhen the world was a more easygoing place.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.51,1:20:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We see in World War II, then, Adolf Hitler.\NWhere did it happen to do his calibrations over here?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.69,1:21:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, there we are.\NAt the end of the war, Adolf Hitler was 45.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.56,1:21:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Stalin was 90.\NHeinrich Himmler, 40.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.81,1:21:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Third Reich itself, 70.\NNeville Chamberlain, when he met Hitler,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.81,1:21:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that was the onset of World War II.\NNeville Chamberlain, you see, was a wishy-washy kind of guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.81,1:21:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, oh, we're going to have peace, and we'll have hearts and flowers,\Nand he said, peace in our time.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.10,1:21:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So when Neville Chamberlain and Hitler\Nshook hands over the agreement, non-aggression pact,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.10,1:21:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what Hitler thought?\NWhat a stupid jerk.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.48,1:21:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He thinks I'm going to live by that.\NHitler thought that, what's his name, that idiot?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.39,1:21:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Neville Chamberlain.\NNeville Chamberlain was an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.39,1:21:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitler thought he was an idiot.\NGod.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.02,1:22:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So I know what Hitler's about.\NHe is like the Komodo dragon.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.82,1:22:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Adolf Hitler and the Komodo dragon calibrate almost exactly the same.\NPoisonous.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.81,1:22:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, the Third Reich.\NSo you can go and see what happened here.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.81,1:22:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you have a recapitulation of World War II.\NYou can see Lord Ha Ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.81,1:22:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that was funny.\NLord Ha Ha was a propagandist.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.81,1:22:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The British or the one over on the German side\Nand used to broadcast propaganda.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.90,1:22:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Over on the left, what have we got here?\NWe got any Tegers people left on the planet?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.90,1:22:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.\NSo what defeated Germany was the 510 of Winston Churchill.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.67,1:22:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,At 510.\NAnd Hitler is 45.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.93,1:22:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,45 cannot stand against 510.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.09,1:22:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Because 510 radiates power.\NWhat did Churchill do for the people?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.89,1:23:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He stood for that which carried people through the London Brits.\NThe power.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.52,1:23:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So the power then does what it does just by standing there.\NWinston Churchill didn't have to do anything at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.61,1:23:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Just had to be there and radiate 510 to the people.\NAnd it gave them the courage to go through the London Blitz and survive.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.61,1:23:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move it to the right again.\NWe see all the bad guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.64,1:23:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't see any more of them.\NAnyway, you can see where America was throughout the thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.77,1:23:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,General MacArthur at 425.\NEverybody thought he was a little arrogant.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.93,1:23:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see where the various embassies were.\NYou can see where Werner Heisenberg was.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.93,1:23:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Werner von Braun, the US military.\NWhat America never quite understands is triage,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.22,1:23:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,which of course was Hiroshima.\NAnd then we see General Rommel at 202, the Luftwaffe.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.47,1:24:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll see that the military generally calibrates higher than the military leaders.\NThe army is integrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.47,1:24:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The army, the kamikaze pilot, is integrous.\NBut Tojo...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.47,1:24:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So the integrous soldier, his patriotism is then abused\Nand he becomes cat and fodder for somebody like Hitler,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.80,1:24:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,who calibrates at 45.\NWe'll do the next and then we'll break for lunch.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.80,1:24:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to finish with war before lunch, aren't we?\NAll right, once you understand now that war comes out of ignorance and delusion,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.81,1:24:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,it's due to the innate incapacity of the human mind.\NOkay, we'll skip more wars.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.10,1:24:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just the example that you can calibrate the truth of anything.\NThis is sort of how you see the observer.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.77,1:25:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Newtonian paradigm.\NIt thinks that this is causing this and this is causing this.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.77,1:25:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,As you get more sophisticated in your understanding of the universe,\Nyou realize that in the nonlinear domain,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.92,1:25:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheldrake's formative causation on the level of consciousness,\Nthis concept is a oneness,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.50,1:25:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,which then demonstrates in the world this way.\NAnd it looks to the world like ABC.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.50,1:25:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The ABC is not happening within the world.\NABC is the sequence of witnessing.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.56,1:25:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Because your consciousness witnesses phenomena sequentially,\Nit says therefore it's happening in the world sequentially.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.65,1:25:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,In the world, nothing is happening sequentially.\NSequence is all a point of observation.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.93,1:25:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean your observations were sequential,\Nbut the oneness, the happening is only a singularity.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.93,1:25:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no such thing as an event or happening in the world.\NThere is only a oneness and a singularity.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.77,1:26:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the holographic phenomena of the oneness,\Nyou walk from here to there and you see it's changing.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.97,1:26:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, oh, this is causing this, this is causing this.\NYou see, that's a phenomena of witnessing.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.97,1:26:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Within the hologram, nothing is causing anything else.\NEverything is just being what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.38,1:26:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you say this thumb is causing the forefinger,\Nwhich is causing the middle finger, causing...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.38,1:26:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is causing anything.\NThat's a sophisticated insight.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.09,1:26:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You get it during meditation.\NYou see that the phenomena itself is not sequential.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.09,1:26:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The witnessing is what's sequential.\NAnd the same thing goes with time.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.22,1:26:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Time doesn't exist as a self-existent reality.\NIt's a sequential of witnessing.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.53,1:26:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Sequence of witnessing.\NYeah, you got one more?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.53,1:26:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll sneak one more in.\NWhat time do we resume?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.14,1:27:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we'll go over it in one minute.\NWhat is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.13,1:27:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, well, we already mentioned this.\NWe talked about the Schroeder equations.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.13,1:27:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We talked about the Heisenberg principle.\NYou can't read this anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.89,1:27:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a very good summation of this on the Internet\Nunder Henry Stapp,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.89,1:27:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,professor of advanced theoretical physics at Berkeley,\Nwho explains by process and process too
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.89,1:27:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,how the Heisenberg process...\NNow, the Heisenberg process isn't just an abstract thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.46,1:27:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, we demonstrated it last night.\NFood, we were served food.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.46,1:27:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It calibrated at 2.05.\NWe calibrated the food.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.10,1:27:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we blessed the food.\NThen it calibrated at 2.10.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.10,1:27:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't that it?\N2.10.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.10,1:27:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so unblessed food calibrates generally at like 2.04, 2.05.\NAnd when you bless it,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.10,1:28:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,if you bless the bejesus out of it, it'll jump to 2.15.\NWe didn't do a big strong one.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.31,1:28:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We were in a public place.\NWe just had a quiet little...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.35,1:28:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still legal, right?\NAs long as you don't say God out loud.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.06,1:28:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We secretly had our...\NAnd it jumped to 8 points.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.25,1:28:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The most stunning example,\Nand then we'll break for lunch.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.72,1:28:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of prayer.\NI'm interested in the verification of spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.94,1:28:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Praying over food actually increases the calibrated level of its energy and power.\NThe most amazing example of that to date that I've discovered is the Ganges River.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.77,1:28:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The Ganges River is the depository of the sewage of over 100 cities and villages along the way.\NIt's full of feces, dead bodies, excrement.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.72,1:29:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It should kill you and be lethal.\NAlong the banks are the ghats where the bodies are burned.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.05,1:29:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The rice of Shiva.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.59,1:29:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You got dead bodies and ashes.\NYou got refuse, garbage, sewage, feces, and animals in the water.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.60,1:29:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, for thousands of years,\Nthe Hindus have blessed the Ganges and bathed in the holy waters.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.72,1:29:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you suppose the Ganges calibrates that?\NThe refuse of 100 cities and villages,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.77,1:29:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,dead people and feces and excrement.\NGanges is over 40.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.21,1:29:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Ganges is over 490.\N500.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.21,1:29:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,501.\N510.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.21,1:29:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,520.\N525.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.21,1:30:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,530.\NThe Ganges River, so help me God, it calibrates at 525.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.85,1:30:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,How can that be?\NIt's like the Ganges River has itself become a saint, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.71,1:30:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the faith and holiness and sacredness and blissingness\Nof millions of people over probably at least a thousand years,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.86,1:30:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, the Aryan civilization in India is, I don't know, 7,000 to 10,000 B.C.\NFor all those millennia, millions and millions of worshippers
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.60,1:30:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in the name of Shiva, you know, have blessed this holy water and sanctified it.\NSo, sanctification then is a function of intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.23,1:30:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Scientific Heisenberg principle.\NScientifically, we can explain.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.03,1:31:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The same process of sanctification.\NAt the same time, the so-called holy lands in the Middle East
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.02,1:31:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,now calibrate like 70 or 80, where the opposite, hatred, venom,\Nthat which comes out of the spleen.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.22,1:31:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Blood conquers hatred.\NBut once were holy lands and probably neutral ground,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.93,1:31:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,they probably calibrated about 200.\NNow it calibrates in the same way.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.93,1:31:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,In the 70s or 80s.\NTherefore, you see, the impact of our consciousness is even measurable
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.03,1:31:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,with its impact on the planet itself.\NThe river was there before mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.48,1:31:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably there after mankind leaves, huh?\NAnd calibrates at such an incredible level.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.31,1:31:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\NAnd yet that which is once holy has been desecrated through hatred.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.02,1:32:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what we hold in consciousness and our intention\Nactually influences the total field.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.01,1:32:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what can we do for mankind?\NWe can be the most forgiving, loving, understanding, compassionate, kind person we can be
Dialogue: 0,1:32:14.73,1:32:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,towards all of life.\NThe reverence for all of life in all of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.57,1:32:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The little black beetle laying on its back and its little legs are...\NHe's saying, help me, help me.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.80,1:32:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You try to walk away and...\NYou have to go back and turn them over.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.80,1:32:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause that's what you have become.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.80,1:32:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NYou have the option to say,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.80,1:32:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and squash them right there.\NI hate beetles, they stink.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.14,1:32:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo, we have the option then,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.18,1:32:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,at all times, at all times.\NAnd here we are on this planet, on this island,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.47,1:33:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,on some trajectory,\Na migration, an evolutionary migration of our spirit.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.47,1:33:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we are blessed by our attitude,\Nall that we encounter.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.68,1:33:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In so doing, we raise the level of the sea.\NAnd by raising the level of the sea,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.72,1:33:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,these people at the bottom of the maps\Nare lifted up by the buoyancy of the water.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:18.72,1:33:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Not by cause and effect.\NGiving them money increases the poverty.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.30,1:33:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In Haiti, the more money you gave them, the worse the poverty got.\NNo, it's not money.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.18,1:33:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a matter of consciousness.\NWhat causes people to be at the bottom
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.18,1:33:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is their level of consciousness.\NSo, what we do for all of mankind is
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.18,1:33:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to be as loving towards all of life as we can be,\Nthereby blessing all of mankind,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.18,1:33:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,thereby raising its level of consciousness,\Nthereby lifting all with us.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.42,1:33:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
